{"title_page": "Ministry of Manpower (Singapore)", "text_new": "<!-- This article is NOT written in US-English. Please do not change it to US-English contrary to [[WP:ENGVAR]]:\n\"An article on a topic that has strong ties to a particular English-speaking nation uses the appropriate variety of English for that nation.\" -->\n<!-- * Article conforms to British English usage (Wikipedia:Manual of Style#National varieties of English) & Day-Month-Year format (Wikipedia:Manual of Style (Singapore-related articles)#Dates). -->\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}}\n{{Infobox Government agency\n|agency_name     = Ministry of Manpower\n|logo            = Ministry of Manpower (Singapore) (logo).png\n|logo_width      = \n|logo_caption    = Logo of the MOM\n|formed          = {{Start date and age|df=yes|1998|04|01}}\n|preceding1      = Ministry of Labour\n|dissolved       =\n|superseding     =\n|jurisdiction    = [[Government of Singapore]]\n|employees       = 2,239 (2018) <ref>https://www.singaporebudget.gov.sg/docs/default-source/budget_2019/download/pdf/43-MOM-2019.pdf </ref>\n|budget          = {{increase}} 1.98 billion ''(est)'' [[SGD]] (2019) <ref>https://www.singaporebudget.gov.sg/docs/default-source/budget_2019/download/pdf/43-MOM-2019.pdf </ref>\n|headquarters    = 18 Havelock Road, Singapore 059764\n|minister1_name  = Mrs [[Josephine Teo]]\n|minister1_pfo   = (Minister of Manpower)\n|minister2_name  = Dr [[Zaqy Mohamad]]\n|minister2_pfo   = (Minister of State)\n|minister3_name  = Mrs [[Low Yen Ling]]\n|minister3_pfo   = (Senior Parliamentary Secretary)\n|chief1_name     = Aubeck Kam\n|chief1_position = Permanent Secretary\n|chief2_name     = Poon Hong Yuen\n|chief2_position = Deputy Secretary (Workforce)\n|chief3_name     = \n|chief3_position = \n|parent_agency   =\n|child1_agency   = [[Central Provident Fund Board]]\n|child2_agency   = [[Singapore Labour Foundation]]\n|child3_agency   = [[Workforce Singapore]]\n|website         = {{url|www.mom.gov.sg}}\n|footnotes       =\n|seal=|chief4_name=|chief4_position=|chief5_name=|chief5_position=|chief6_name=|chief6_position=|chief7_name=|chief7_position=|chief8_name=|chief8_position=|chief9_name=|chief9_position=|parent_department=}}\nThe '''Ministry of Manpower''' ([[Abbreviation]]: '''MOM'''; {{lang-ms|Kementerian Tenaga Manusia}}; [[Tamil language|Tamil]]: {{lang|ta| \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bb3 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1}}; [[Simplified Chinese|Chinese]]: {{lang|zh|\u65b0\u52a0\u5761\u4eba\u529b\u90e8}}) is a [[ministry (government department)|ministry]] of the [[Government of Singapore]] which is responsible for the formulation and implementation of labour policies related to the [[workforce]] in Singapore. The Ministry was known as Ministry of Labour until 1998. \n\nSingapore is ranked first among 157 countries in the inaugural World Bank Human Capital Index (HCI), which measures the human capital that a child born today can expect to attain by the age of 18.<ref>{{cite news|title=Asian countries dominate World Bank's new index of investment in 'human capital' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2018/oct/11/asian-countries-dominate-world-banks-new-index-of-investment-in-human-capital|newspaper=the Guardian}}</ref> In the IMD World Talent Ranking 2018, Singapore maintained its position as the best nation in Asia and 13th globally in developing, attracting and retaining highly-skilled professionals.<ref>{{cite news|title=These countries are best at attracting and nurturing talented workers|url=https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2018/11/countries-best-at-attracting-and-nurturing-talented-workers|newspaper=WEF}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Singapore placed 13th in World Talent Rankings, best in Asia Pacific|url=https://sg.finance.yahoo.com/news/singapore-placed-13th-world-talent-rankings-best-asia-pacific-030448198.html|newspaper=Yahoo news}}</ref>\n\n==Statutory Boards==\n[[Image:Ministry of Manpower 2, Mar 06.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Ministry of Manpower building at Havelock Road, Singapore.]]\nThe MOM oversees 15 divisions and 3 statutory boards.<ref>{{cite web|title=Divisions and statutory boards|url=http://www.mom.gov.sg/about-us/divisions-and-statutory-boards|website=Ministry of Manpower (MOM) Singapore|accessdate=7 May 2018}}</ref> These are:\n* Corporate Communications Department\n* Corporate Planning Department\n* Customer Responsiveness Department\n* Foreign Manpower Management Division\n* Human Resource Department\n* Income Security Policy Division\n* International Manpower Division\n* Labour Relations and Workplaces Division\n* Legal Services Department\n* Manpower Planning and Policy Division\n* Manpower Research and Statistics Department\n* Occupational Safety and Health Division\n* National Human Resources Division\n* Work Pass Division\n* Workplace Policy and Strategy Division\n* MOM Statutory Board\n** [[Central Provident Fund Board]]\n** [[Singapore Workforce Development Agency]]\n** [[Singapore Labour Foundation]]\n\n==Minister for Manpower==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:40%\"\n! width= 30% | Years in Office\n! width= 70% | Minister\n! width= 30% | Political Party\n|-\n| '''1963 \u2013 1968''' || [[Jek Yeun Thong]] ||rowspan=\"14\"| {{SG/PAP}}\n|-\n| '''1968 - 1971''' || [[S Rajaratnam]]\n|-\n| '''1971 - 1981''' || [[Ong Pang Boon]]\n|-\n| '''1981 - 1983''' || [[Ong Teng Cheong]]\n|-\n| '''1983 - 1983''' || [[E W Barker]]\n|-\n| '''1983 - 1985''' || [[S Jayakumar]]\n|-\n| '''1985 - 1991''' || [[Lee Yock Suan]]\n|-\n| '''1992 - 2003''' || [[Lee Boon Yang]]\n|-\n| '''2003 - 2008''' || [[Ng Eng Hen]]\n|-\n| '''2008 - 2011''' || [[Gan Kim Yong]]\n|-\n| '''2011 - 2012''' || [[Tharman Shanmugaratnam]]\n|-\n| '''2012 - 2015 '''|| [[Tan Chuan-Jin]]\n|-\n| '''2015 - 2018''' || [[Lim Swee Say]]\n|-\n| '''2018-Incumbent''' || [[Josephine Teo]]\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Central Provident Fund Board]]\n* [[Employment in Singapore]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Ministry of Manpower (Singapore)}}\n*{{Official website|http://www.mom.gov.sg/ Ministry of Manpower (Singapore)}}\n\n{{Government of Singapore}}\n{{Singapore topics}}\n\n[[Category:1998 in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Government ministries of Singapore]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- This article is NOT written in US-English. Please do not change it to US-English contrary to [[WP:ENGVAR]]:\n\"An article on a topic that has strong ties to a particular English-speaking nation uses the appropriate variety of English for that nation.\" -->\n<!-- * Article conforms to British English usage (Wikipedia:Manual of Style#National varieties of English) & Day-Month-Year format (Wikipedia:Manual of Style (Singapore-related articles)#Dates). -->\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}}\n{{Infobox Government agency\n|agency_name     = Ministry of Manpower\n|logo            = Ministry of Manpower (Singapore) (logo).png\n|logo_width      = \n|logo_caption    = Logo of the MOM\n|formed          =\n|preceding1      =\n|dissolved       =\n|superseding     =\n|jurisdiction    = [[Government of Singapore]]\n|employees       = 2,239 (2018) <ref>https://www.singaporebudget.gov.sg/docs/default-source/budget_2019/download/pdf/43-MOM-2019.pdf </ref>\n|budget          = {{increase}} 1.98 billion ''(est)'' [[SGD]] (2019) <ref>https://www.singaporebudget.gov.sg/docs/default-source/budget_2019/download/pdf/43-MOM-2019.pdf </ref>\n|headquarters    = 18 Havelock Road, Singapore 059764\n|minister1_name  = Mrs [[Josephine Teo]]\n|minister1_pfo   = (Minister of Manpower)\n|minister2_name  = Dr [[Zaqy Mohamad]]\n|minister2_pfo   = (Minister of State)\n|minister3_name  = Mrs [[Low Yen Ling]]\n|minister3_pfo   = (Senior Parliamentary Secretary)\n|chief1_name     = Aubeck Kam\n|chief1_position = Permanent Secretary\n|chief2_name     = Poon Hong Yuen\n|chief2_position = Deputy Secretary (Workforce)\n|chief3_name     = \n|chief3_position = \n|parent_agency   =\n|child1_agency   = [[Central Provident Fund Board]]\n|child2_agency   = 