{"title_page": "Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox government agency\n|agency_name = '''Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority'''\n|nativename =\n|abbreviation = UMRA\n|logo =\n|logo_width = 160px\n|logo_caption =\n|seal = \n|seal_width = 140px\n|seal_caption =\n|formed = {{birth year and age|2017}}\n|jurisdiction = [[Government of Uganda]]\n|headquarters = [[Kampala]], [[Uganda]]\n|employees = \n|budget = \n|chief1_name =[[Chairperson]]\n|chief1_position = <br/>'''Jacqueline Mbabazi'''\n|chief2_name = [[Executive Director]]\n|chief2_position =<br/> '''Edith Namugga Tusuubira'''<ref name=\"Zero\">{{cite web|title=Tusuubira Appointed UMRA Executive Director  |newspaper=[[New Vision]] | date=24 August 2019 | url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1506152/tusuubira-appointed-umra-executive-director|access-date=25 August 2019 | author=John Semakula |place=Kampala}}</ref> \n|parent_agency = [[Ministry of Finance, Planning and Economic Development (Uganda)|Uganda Ministry of Finance, Planning and Economic Development]] \n|website = {{URL|www.umra.go.ug/}}\n|footnotes =\n}}\n\nThe '''Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority''' ('''UMRA'''),  is a government agency responsible for the licensing, supervision and regulation of Tier-4 micro finance institutions, money lenders, savings cooperatives and any money-lending institution with capital of less that USh500 million (US$140,000). Tier-4 institutions are those that do not accept financial deposits and are not under the supervision of the [[Bank of Uganda]], the [[central bank]] and national banking regulator.<ref name=\"One\">{{cite web|title=Ministry of Finance, Planning & Economic Development: Launching of the Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority (UMRA) |newspaper=[[Daily Monitor]] |location=Kampala |url=http://web.monitor.co.ug/Supplement/2017/12/finance-11122017.pdf |format=PDF |access-date=21 April 2018 |date=11 December 2017 |author=Newspaper Supplement}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nAs far back as 2013, the [[government of Uganda]] announced its intentions to create a government agency to regulate money lenders who were not regulated by the central bank.<ref name=\"Two\">{{cite web|newspaper=[[New Vision]] |location=Kampla | url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1334518/microfinance-regulatory-body-offing |title=Microfinance regulatory body in the offing |access-date=21 April 2018 |date=13 November 2013 |  first=Oyet |last=Okwera}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2016, the [[Parliament of Uganda]] passed the Tier IV Microfinance Institutions Act, to take effect on 1 July 2017. The establishment of the UMRA was a key provision of the Act. UMRA is expected to promote a sound and sustainable non-banking financial institution\u2019s sector and offer financial consumer protection and financial  inclusion, financial stability, and protection among the low income population in Uganda.<ref name=\"Three\">{{cite web|access-date=21 April 2018 |publisher=Firstinitiative.org | url=https://www.firstinitiative.org/projects/umra-tier-vi-regulation-uganda |title=UMRA Tier VI Regulation in Uganda: Project Development Objective (PDO) |last=First Initiative Organization |date=2015}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nUMRA came into existence on 1 January 2017.<ref name=\"Four\">{{cite web|title=Microfinance Institutions and Money Lenders Under the Control of the Ugandan State |date=30 August 2017 | url=https://juriafrique.com/eng/2017/08/30/microfinance-institutions-and-money-lenders-under-the-control-of-the-ugandan-state/ |access-date=21 April 2018 |publisher=Juriafrique.com | author=JuriAfrica}}</ref> The new institution regulates money lending between Ugandans and the hitherto non-regulated Tier-4 microfinance institutions and other private money lenders. It also authorizes the Minister of State for Microfinance, to set the interest rates which moneylenders should charge borrowers.<ref name=\"Five\">{{cite web|author=Lydia Namono Wesonga |\nurl=http://www.monitor.co.ug/Business/Law-to-regulate-moneylenders-takes-effect-July/688322-3975848-54wiwf/index.html | title=Law to regulate moneylenders takes effect July |\ndate=19 June 2017 |access-date=21 April 2018 |location=Kampala |newspaper=[[Daily Monitor]]}}</ref> On 8 December 2017, the State Minister of Finance for Microfinance, [[Haruna Kasolo Kyeyune]] inaugurated the [[board of directors]], including its [[chairperson]] and [[executive director]].<ref name=\"One\"/>\n\n==Administration==\nOn 8 December 2017, the following seven individuals were appointed to the board of directors of the Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority:<ref name=\"One\"/>\n\n# [[Jacqueline Mbabazi]]: [[Chairperson]]\n# [[Edith Namugga Tusuubira]]: [[Executive Director]]<ref name=\"Zero\"/>\n# [[Joyce Okello]]: Member\n# [[Charles Olenyi]]: Member\n# [[Ndyanabo Richard Kirungi]]: Member \n# [[Bob Barigye Bariyo]]: Member\n# [[Naome Kibaaju]]: Member.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Economy of Uganda]]\n*[[Ministry of Finance, Planning and Economic Development (Uganda)|Uganda Ministry of Finance, Planning & Economic Development]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.umra.go.ug Website of Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority (UMRA)]\n\n[[Category:Government agencies of Uganda]]\n[[Category:Economy of Uganda]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 2017]]\n[[Category:2017 establishments in Uganda]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Kampala]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox government agency\n|agency_name = '''Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority'''\n|nativename =\n|abbreviation = UMRA\n|logo =\n|logo_width = 160px\n|logo_caption =\n|seal = \n|seal_width = 140px\n|seal_caption =\n|formed = {{birth year and age|2017}}\n|jurisdiction = [[Government of Uganda]]\n|headquarters = [[Kampala]], [[Uganda]]\n|employees = \n|budget = \n|chief1_name =[[Chairperson]]\n|chief1_position = <br/>'''Jacqueline Mbabazi'''\n|chief2_name = [[Executive Director]]\n|chief2_position =<br/> '''Edith Namugga Tusuubira'''<ref name=\"Zero\">{{cite web|title=Tusuubira Appointed UMRA Executive Director  |newspaper=[[New Vision]] | date=24 August 2019 | url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1506152/tusuubira-appointed-umra-executive-director|access-date=25 August 2019 | author=John Semakula |place=Kampala}}</ref> \n|parent_agency = [[Ministry of Finance, Planning and Economic Development (Uganda)|Uganda Ministry of Finance, Planning and Economic Development]] \n|website = {{URL|www.umra.go.ug/}}\n|footnotes =\n}}\n\nThe '''Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority''' ('''UMRA'''),  is a government agency responsible for the licensing, supervision and regulation of Tier-4 micro finance institutions, money lenders, savings cooperatives and any money-lending institution with capital of less that USh500 million (US$140,000). Tier-4 institutions are those that do not accept financial deposits and are not under the supervision of the [[Bank of Uganda]], the [[central bank]] and national banking regulator.<ref name=\"One\">{{cite web|title=Ministry of Finance, Planning & Economic Development: Launching of the Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority (UMRA) |newspaper=[[Daily Monitor]] |location=Kampala |url=http://web.monitor.co.ug/Supplement/2017/12/finance-11122017.pdf |format=PDF |access-date=21 April 2018 |date=11 December 2017 |author=Newspaper Supplement}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nAs far back as 2013, the [[government of Uganda]] announced its intentions to create a government agency to regulate money lenders who were not regulated by the central bank.<ref name=\"Two\">{{cite web|newspaper=[[New Vision]] |location=Kampla | url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1334518/microfinance-regulatory-body-offing |title=Microfinance regulatory body in the offing |access-date=21 April 2018 |date=13 November 2013 |  first=Oyet |last=Okwera}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2016, the [[Parliament of Uganda]] passed the Tier IV Microfinance Institutions Act, to take effect on 1 July 2017. The establishment of the UMRA was a key provision of the Act. UMRA is expected to promote a sound and sustainable non-banking financial institution\u2019s sector and offer financial consumer protection and financial  inclusion, financial stability, and protection among the low income population in Uganda.<ref name=\"Three\">{{cite web|access-date=21 April 2018 |publisher=Firstinitiative.org | url=https://www.firstinitiative.org/projects/umra-tier-vi-regulation-uganda |title=UMRA Tier VI Regulation in Uganda: Project Development Objective (PDO) |last=First Initiative Organization |date=2015}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nUMRA came into existence on 1 January 2017.<ref name=\"Four\">{{cite web|title=Microfinance Institutions and Money Lenders Under the Control of the Ugandan State |date=30 August 2017 | url=https://juriafrique.com/eng/2017/08/30/microfinance-institutions-and-money-lenders-under-the-control-of-the-ugandan-state/ |access-date=21 April 2018 |publisher=Juriafrique.com | author=JuriAfrica}}</ref> The new institution regulates money lending between Ugandans and the hitherto non-regulated Tier-4 microfinance institutions and other private money lenders. It also authorizes the Minister of State for Microfinance, to set the interest rates which moneylenders should charge borrowers.<ref name=\"Five\">{{cite web|author=Lydia Namono Wesonga |\nurl=http://www.monitor.co.ug/Business/Law-to-regulate-moneylenders-takes-effect-July/688322-3975848-54wiwf/index.html | title=Law to regulate moneylenders takes effect July |\ndate=19 June 2017 |access-date=21 April 2018 |location=Kampala |newspaper=[[Daily Monitor]]}}</ref> On 8 December 2017, the State Minister of Finance for Microfinance, [[Haruna Kasolo Kyeyune]] inaugurated the [[board of directors]], including its [[chairperson]] and [[executive director]].<ref name=\"One\"/>\n\n==Administration==\nOn 8 December, the following seven individuals were appointed to the board of directors of the Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority:<ref name=\"One\"/>\n\n# [[Jacqueline Mbabazi]]: [[Chairperson]]\n# [[Edith Namugga Tusuubira]]: [[Executive Director]]<ref name=\"Zero\"/>\n# [[Joyce Okello]]: Member\n# [[Charles Olenyi]]: Member\n# [[Ndyanabo Richard Kirungi]]: Member \n# [[Bob Barigye Bariyo]]: Member\n# [[Naome Kibaaju]]: Member.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Economy of Uganda]]\n*[[Ministry of Finance, Planning and Economic Development (Uganda)|Uganda Ministry of Finance, Planning & Economic Development]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.umra.go.ug Website of Uganda Microfinance Regulatory Authority (UMRA)]\n\n[[Category:Government agencies of Uganda]]\n[[Category:Economy of Uganda]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 2017]]\n[[Category:2017 establishments in Uganda]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Kampala]]\n", "name_user": "Greyjoy", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAdministration", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uganda_Microfinance_Regulatory_Authority"}
